betterquesting:10.desc:8:
This pack is mainly focused on well known mod §bGregTech§r, that recently got ported to version 1.12.2 with acronym §bGTCE§r meaning Community Edtion.
 
This brought me to idea of making this pack that implements mods along side of GT using similar recipe structure to make progression a bit harder. There are many mods you may know from other modpacks however with significantly different recipes and behavior.
 
Any issues or questsions encountered during gampley can be discussed on §cCurseForge§r modpack's issues tab or at our official §1Discord§r server.
 
Hope you will enjoy this pack and don't forget to tell friends about this pack. 
§4Good luck you're going to need it!

There are few modes that can be applied in order to make the pack a bit §4harder §ror a bit §aeasier!§r

There are not any major changes to gameplay except some recipes that can be easier or harder depending on your preferences. 
List of available modes can be found here: 
§4Packmode no.1
§4Packmode no.2
§4Packmode no.3§r

You can change the modes in options or using command §c/packmode mode_name§r.

§b§nServer Owners§r
In order to apply packmode for your server issue packmode command in your console!

Since this modpack contains many changed recipes and many ways to craft certain things you will need to get yourself familiar with mod called

§cJust Enough Items§r that adds sidebar in inventory gui which you can use to lookup for certain stuff and recipes.

If you accidentaly hide it use key combination of §b CTRL + O§r to bring that back.

You can list things from specific mod by using §b@§r prefix and then modid forex. (@gregtech)

Food is really important here!
Because it really matter what you eat and how well you take care about your hunger and nutritions.

§4Spice of Life§r - You cannot eat same thing over and over again so prepare yourself for quite a big farming part.

Of course there are amyn mods with additional food and crops like well known 
§cPam's Harvestcraft§r!

§6Friendly tip:§r
Start your journey by collecting as many crops/food as you can!

FTB Utilities is basically §bEssentials§r for Forge! It adds many useful commands, you will definitely use during this playthrough.

§c§l§nCommands:§r
§a/sethome§r - Sets place as your home after that you can use home command! You can have multiple homes by putting name after command.
§a/home§r - Teleports you to your home.
§a/setwarp§r - Sets place as warp, basically public place for everyone to teleport to! Requires uniqe name.
§a/warp§r - Teleports you specific warp.

§c§l§nProtection:§r
Yes, you can claim chunks and set protection against other players.
Open §aChunks GUI§r by clicking map icon in the top left corner of your inventory screen.
You can claim chunks by leftclick on specific place or hold and drag to claim more chunks at once.

§c§l§nChunkloading:§r
You can chunkload by shift-left clicking on chunk you claim!
Chunk will keep loaded in memory regardless if you're in the chunk or not.

This first chapter is basically about vanilla stuff.
 As you will progress further you will definitely notice significant changes in recipes and gameplay. 
 
This questbook will guide you through this pack and mods included in this pack.

Well that's right we're gonna start your journey by collecting some flints and sticks...
Yeah i know this might be similar to many other packs but trust me!
 
After you collect some §7Flints§r and some §cSticks§r. Take those §7Flints§r and hit them against some rock and you'll get §8Flake flint§r!
 
You can now switch to next task and craft flint tools.
 
§6Man these are really great for beginning!

§8§lGregTech §7Flint Tools §rare really great stuff to begin with!
 
They have pretty decent stats for flint tools yet they have some handy abilities.
 
For example §8GT Axes§r has ability to chop down whole tree.

I bet you tried crafting logs into planks!
So for you to chop logs into planks you need §cCutting Board§r!
 
§4§l§nWorking with Cutting Board§r
- Firs off place cutting board on the ground.
- Take any logs you have an right click on cutting board with them.
- Grab Axe and left click on cutting board. (You may see progress on top of your screen)
Basic info about this pack and some useful features you can use.
Oh that sweet moment when you started this pack for the fisrt time!
